::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 501030203: Config/Level/Mission/5010302/Act/Act501030203.json-->
::'''Clara:''' Oh... of course, {{MC|f=Miss|m=Sir}}. What do you wish to talk about?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_501030201_16-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_501030201_16-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What sort of place is the Robot Settlement?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501030208-->
:::'''Clara:''' It's... It used to be a manned well shaft for Mr. Svarog. If the cable car line wasn't open, this would be the only way to the surface around here.
:::'''Clara:''' The Fragmentum disaster caused many to lose their homes...
:::'''Clara:''' In the beginning, some would come here in hopes of receiving Mr. Svarog's protection.
:::'''Clara:''' And so... Clara got together with Mr. Svarog to provide supplies to refugees. They also let them stay around the well shaft. This way, Mr. Svarog could help everyone fend off the Fragmentum's monsters.
:::'''Clara:''' Slowly but surely, many heard about how Mr. Svarog could protect people, and came here to make camp...
:::'''Clara:''' ...and that's how the Robot Settlement developed into such a bastion.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_501030201_24-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_501030201_24-->
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why is it called the Robot Settlement?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501030215-->
::::'''Clara:''' Ah, I forgot to mention this...!
::::'''Clara:''' Actually... it's because this place used to be where Mr. Svarog and the Little Robots of his robot network were stationed.
::::'''Clara:''' Most of the vagrants who make camp here liked these robots... As time went by, they also learned some mechanical skills.
::::'''Clara:''' Everyone was so kind... Humans and robots, living in harmony here. And that's why everyone called this place the Robot Settlement.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Everyone depends on Clara and Svarog's salvation, then?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501030220-->
::::'''Clara:''' Um... that's not true.
::::'''Clara:''' The people who live here all have their own skills... Like mechanical maintenance and such.
::::'''Clara:''' Everyone... should be able to live their lives by relying on themselves. But the Underworld is sorely lacking in supplies now...
::::'''Clara:''' And so, to prevent everyone from starving or falling ill... Clara and Mr. Svarog must always have supplies handy.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Return}} I've got it. Thank you Clara.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501030225-->
::::'''Clara:''' Heehee, all in a day's work.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What's your relationship with Svarog like?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501030227-->
:::'''Clara:''' Well, if I had to say... more like family?
:::'''Clara:''' I've never met my own parents... For as long as I can remember, Mr. Svarog's always been by my side.
:::'''Clara:''' No matter what we faced, Mr. Svarog would always put my well-being first... He also taught me all sorts of things, and how to live with others...
:::'''Clara:''' I think... Mr. Svarog is like what people call... a "father."
:::'''Clara:''' So... Mr. Svarog and I are family. I think... that's the right word?
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} We'll end the talk here for now.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501030233-->
:::'''Clara:''' Oh... okay.
